1
00:01:06,088 --> 00:01:08,132
Did Paolo send you?

2
00:01:10,509 --> 00:01:11,635
Perhaps.

3
00:01:46,754 --> 00:01:48,630
Paolo told me

4
00:01:48,714 --> 00:01:51,049
to give you a painless death

5
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:54,803
if you show respect to Paolo.

6
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:05,230
Relay this message to Paolo.
I will not respect him

7
00:02:06,857 --> 00:02:08,734
even after I die.

8
00:03:24,977 --> 00:03:25,894
Inzaghi?

9
00:03:28,856 --> 00:03:29,940
Inzaghi.

10
00:04:02,389 --> 00:04:04,016
Did you get the rooftop ready?

11
00:04:04,516 --> 00:04:06,226
-Well, yes.
-Good.

12
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:08,812
Wait. Why don't we drink in the office?

13
00:04:08,896 --> 00:04:11,356
There's so much pigeon poop
on the rooftop.

14
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,733
Let me carry that.

15
00:04:14,276 --> 00:04:16,486
I bet it was Inzaghi
and the other pigeons.

16
00:04:20,574 --> 00:04:23,785
Inzaghi is not that kind of pigeon.

17
00:04:23,869 --> 00:04:26,455
I bet it was other pigeons.
Don't badmouth Inzaghi.

18
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,540
It would hurt Inzaghi.

19
00:04:34,963 --> 00:04:36,173
What happened here?

20
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:41,678
A nail must have torn it
when I was moving the table.

21
00:04:42,262 --> 00:04:45,098
Why did you move that by yourself?
Let's drink standing up.

22
00:04:45,182 --> 00:04:46,308
-Ms. Hong.
-What?

23
00:04:47,559 --> 00:04:50,187
My knees are aching.

24
00:04:51,063 --> 00:04:52,689
Can we drink sitting down?

25
00:04:54,107 --> 00:04:55,275
Sure.

26
00:04:58,236 --> 00:05:01,448
Did you send the file from the gallery
to Prosecutor Jung?

27
00:05:02,074 --> 00:05:04,326
Yes. He should be
on his way to make the arrest.

28
00:05:04,409 --> 00:05:05,452
That's great.

29
00:05:08,538 --> 00:05:11,917
Why would you hold such a stupid event
and cause so much trouble?

30
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,960
The gallery is not your playground!

31
00:05:15,212 --> 00:05:16,171
I'm sorry.

32
00:05:16,254 --> 00:05:18,006
I'm so sorry, sir.

33
00:05:19,257 --> 00:05:21,301
This won't end with you.

34
00:05:21,385 --> 00:05:22,427
I…

35
00:05:23,679 --> 00:05:24,721
Be quiet.

36
00:05:25,722 --> 00:05:27,140
I'm thinking.

37
00:05:27,224 --> 00:05:29,518
This is ridiculous.

38
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:32,646
It's like she doesn't think at all.

39
00:05:33,522 --> 00:05:36,608
You should leave the country
before they bar you from going abroad.

40
00:05:36,692 --> 00:05:37,984
Why? Go where?

41
00:05:38,068 --> 00:05:39,986
I'll take the fall for him. Why bother?

42
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:43,573
All the evidence they have points to you.

43
00:05:43,657 --> 00:05:47,452
They will be able to track the IP address
from the gallery to your home.

44
00:05:51,581 --> 00:05:52,708
Han-seo.

45
00:05:53,917 --> 00:05:56,461
Get me the earliest flight
leaving for New York now.

46
00:05:57,212 --> 00:05:58,130
Yes, sir.

47
00:06:29,619 --> 00:06:30,871
Before I leave,

48
00:06:30,954 --> 00:06:33,040
I want to see Vincenzo's dead body.

49
00:06:40,714 --> 00:06:42,632
Yes, sir. We took care of it.

50
00:06:43,425 --> 00:06:45,594
But I found Choi Myung-hee's phone number

51
00:06:45,677 --> 00:06:47,971
in the call history
on one of the cell phones.

52
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:54,811
Okay. Well done. Wrap it up.

53
00:07:03,695 --> 00:07:06,281
-Yes. Mr. Consigliere.
-Hey, Luca.

54
00:07:37,187 --> 00:07:39,523
RESTRICTED NUMBER

55
00:07:43,819 --> 00:07:45,195
They failed again.

56
00:07:53,328 --> 00:07:56,206
He's so hard to kill.

57
00:08:04,798 --> 00:08:07,467
And they call themselves
the Mafia's hitmen?

58
00:08:07,551 --> 00:08:10,470
They look like the thieves
from Home Alone. Look at the feather.

59
00:08:10,554 --> 00:08:11,805
Ms. Choi Myung-hee!

60
00:08:11,888 --> 00:08:13,181
What will you do about it?

61
00:08:19,938 --> 00:08:23,692
I'm sorry, sir. Let's go
to the airport now. I'll escort you.

62
00:08:39,207 --> 00:08:40,458
Stop them now.

63
00:08:42,627 --> 00:08:43,628
Forget it.

64
00:08:56,975 --> 00:08:58,810
ARREST WARRANT

65
00:09:02,063 --> 00:09:04,107
I came personally
to mark this historical day.

66
00:09:04,191 --> 00:09:06,026
You seem very happy.

67
00:09:06,109 --> 00:09:07,444
Why wouldn't I be?

68
00:09:08,028 --> 00:09:09,070
Take him.

69
00:09:11,281 --> 00:09:13,617
I'll come to you as soon as I'm ready.

70
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:14,302
Inzaghi.

71
00:10:17,097 --> 00:10:20,058
Were you returning the favor?

72
00:10:21,601 --> 00:10:22,519
Were you?

73
00:10:24,437 --> 00:10:25,313
Is that it?

74
00:10:30,151 --> 00:10:31,945
No way. It can't be.

75
00:10:33,029 --> 00:10:35,323
How can a pigeon save a man?

76
00:10:59,681 --> 00:11:01,558
There's a news embargo.

77
00:11:01,641 --> 00:11:03,393
Jang Han-seok's been arrested.

78
00:11:03,476 --> 00:11:06,980
Prosecutor Jung will announce it
at a press conference tomorrow morning.

79
00:11:09,357 --> 00:11:10,900
Good job.

80
00:11:18,324 --> 00:11:19,409
This is beautiful.

81
00:11:27,459 --> 00:11:30,170
Goodness. Thank you, Ms. Oh.

82
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:36,634
You wrote a letter, too?

83
00:11:36,718 --> 00:11:39,012
Hold on. Not now.

84
00:11:39,095 --> 00:11:40,722
Please read it at home.

85
00:12:26,351 --> 00:12:27,811
-Hello.
-Hello.

86
00:12:27,894 --> 00:12:29,479
-Hi.
-You're here.

87
00:12:30,814 --> 00:12:33,066
Ms. Hong, isn't it safe to say

88
00:12:33,817 --> 00:12:37,112
that it was all thanks to us
that Babel's chairman was arrested?

89
00:12:37,195 --> 00:12:40,657
Yes. Thanks to your help,
we were able to catch Chairman Jang!

90
00:12:41,324 --> 00:12:44,410
Prosecutor Jung In-kuk will
now begin the press conference

91
00:12:44,494 --> 00:12:47,705
-All right. It's starting.
-about the investigation against Babel.

92
00:12:54,796 --> 00:12:56,506
-Hello.
-He's on.

93
00:12:56,589 --> 00:12:59,551
I'm Prosecutor Jung In-kuk of
Seoul Namdongbu Prosecutors' Office.

94
00:12:59,634 --> 00:13:00,760
There he is.

95
00:13:01,719 --> 00:13:05,849
I have been investigating Babel Group on
six different charges for the past year.

96
00:13:05,932 --> 00:13:08,268
They're all depraved
corporate corruption charges.

97
00:13:08,351 --> 00:13:12,188
The charges violated the national economic
system and legal system.

98
00:13:12,272 --> 00:13:14,107
That's it! There you go!

99
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:15,692
That hits the spot.

100
00:13:15,775 --> 00:13:19,737
But I must tell the truth now.

101
00:13:22,115 --> 00:13:23,867
When Jang Guk-hwan was the chairman,

102
00:13:23,950 --> 00:13:26,161
I was eager to make a name for myself

103
00:13:26,244 --> 00:13:27,954
and took my investigation too far.

104
00:13:28,037 --> 00:13:29,372
As a result, I was demoted.

105
00:13:31,332 --> 00:13:33,543
My personal feelings got the better of me.

106
00:13:33,626 --> 00:13:35,545
I tried to indict Chairman Jang Han-seok

107
00:13:35,628 --> 00:13:38,715
of Babel with unproven claims.

108
00:13:38,798 --> 00:13:40,341
What's he saying? Has he gone mad?

109
00:13:41,134 --> 00:13:43,219
And I crossed the line again
and caused damage

110
00:13:43,303 --> 00:13:45,305
to the Babel Group
with yesterday's incident.

111
00:13:45,388 --> 00:13:46,973
Is that really Mr. Jung?

112
00:13:48,725 --> 00:13:51,352
It looks like he switched sides.

113
00:13:51,936 --> 00:13:54,314
So he betrayed us?

114
00:13:56,524 --> 00:14:00,361
I am holding this press conference
to come clean about my wrongdoings

115
00:14:00,445 --> 00:14:03,656
and to recover the trust
the Namdongbu office has lost.

116
00:14:05,116 --> 00:14:08,036
From now on, I will serve the people
of our country without

117
00:14:08,119 --> 00:14:10,872
-letting my emotions get the better of me.
-I didn't see this coming.

118
00:14:10,955 --> 00:14:12,874
If this happened in a drama,

119
00:14:12,957 --> 00:14:15,001
people would say it's too unrealistic.

120
00:14:15,627 --> 00:14:16,794
Moreover,

121
00:14:16,878 --> 00:14:18,546
-They'd be up in arms about it.
-my ambition

122
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:22,091
has deeply mistreated
Chairman Jang Han-seok of Babel.

123
00:14:22,759 --> 00:14:25,303
I would like to apologize for my actions.

124
00:14:25,386 --> 00:14:26,596
That's okay.

125
00:14:28,097 --> 00:14:31,100
I knew he was going to cave in
like that in the end.

126
00:14:31,184 --> 00:14:32,894
That arrogant jerk.

127
00:14:32,977 --> 00:14:36,022
NAMDONGBU OFFICE PRESS CONFERENCE
ON THE BABEL INVESTIGATION

128
00:14:36,105 --> 00:14:39,692
You should apologize to me, too!
That greedy bastard…

129
00:14:41,694 --> 00:14:43,446
Look at him bowing down like that.

130
00:14:45,073 --> 00:14:48,576
As of today, all the charges
against Babel will be dropped,

131
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,370
and the investigation will be closed.

132
00:14:50,995 --> 00:14:53,873
I would like to apologize
for the confusion I've caused.

133
00:15:13,726 --> 00:15:14,811
Ms. Hong.

134
00:15:19,482 --> 00:15:20,483
Gosh.

135
00:15:21,442 --> 00:15:22,777
Let's visit him later.

136
00:15:24,112 --> 00:15:26,030
I should go and slap him.

137
00:15:27,824 --> 00:15:29,200
He won't see us anyway.

138
00:15:30,076 --> 00:15:31,202
We'll go later.

139
00:15:35,081 --> 00:15:37,041
This is unbelievably cruel.

140
00:15:38,459 --> 00:15:42,213
He despised Babel.
How could he switch sides overnight?

141
00:16:03,651 --> 00:16:05,737
Why didn't we see this coming?

142
00:16:11,909 --> 00:16:13,411
You can dodge a flying dagger,

143
00:16:14,954 --> 00:16:16,914
but you can't dodge a hidden dagger.

144
00:16:20,043 --> 00:16:21,753
Aren't you angry?

145
00:16:22,337 --> 00:16:23,296
Angry?

146
00:16:27,008 --> 00:16:28,176
I'm furious.

147
00:16:29,844 --> 00:16:31,596
I'm just used to it.

148
00:16:40,605 --> 00:16:42,607
I'll make him pay for this.

149
00:16:43,816 --> 00:16:45,276
He'll pay no matter what.

150
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:48,237
If we react emotionally to betrayals,
it'll end up hurting us.

151
00:16:49,447 --> 00:16:50,782
The bigger the betrayal is,

152
00:16:53,326 --> 00:16:54,911
the more careful we must be.

153
00:17:03,294 --> 00:17:07,048
If you were going to do this anyway,
you should've gone easy on them.

154
00:17:08,925 --> 00:17:11,427
I'm sorry for my reckless behavior, sir.

155
00:17:14,764 --> 00:17:18,309
I'll suspend you for two weeks
as a formality.

156
00:17:18,393 --> 00:17:19,310
Take a breather.

157
00:17:19,894 --> 00:17:22,438
When you return, you'll be promoted.

158
00:17:22,522 --> 00:17:23,439
For your office…

159
00:17:23,523 --> 00:17:25,858
Take Mr. Seo's office.
Make yourself at home.

160
00:17:26,901 --> 00:17:28,361
Okay. Thank you.

161
00:17:28,444 --> 00:17:30,071
Anything else you need?

162
00:17:30,154 --> 00:17:33,574
Could you put some guards
around me and my family?

163
00:17:34,617 --> 00:17:36,411
The Mafia might be gunning for me.

164
00:17:40,456 --> 00:17:41,666
Let's go.

165
00:17:45,878 --> 00:17:50,133
You know that I obtained
some hard evidence today, don't you?

166
00:17:52,301 --> 00:17:54,595
There's no way out for you this time.

167
00:18:00,351 --> 00:18:03,396
But what if I make this all go away?

168
00:18:05,898 --> 00:18:07,400
How high can I go?

169
00:18:09,527 --> 00:18:11,237
I'm serious right now.

170
00:18:14,282 --> 00:18:16,200
Gosh. Is this some kind of prank?

171
00:18:18,578 --> 00:18:19,829
Why all of a sudden?

172
00:18:20,455 --> 00:18:21,998
Since it's finally time.

173
00:18:22,081 --> 00:18:25,001
Then why have you been
harassing me all this time?

174
00:18:25,084 --> 00:18:29,964
Because I needed Vincenzo to bring me
the best evidence, like today.

175
00:18:31,758 --> 00:18:33,009
Let me ask you again.

176
00:18:34,594 --> 00:18:36,012
How high can I go?

177
00:18:36,095 --> 00:18:37,555
I can make you the Chief Prosecutor.

178
00:18:37,638 --> 00:18:39,348
Make me the Prosecutor General…

179
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:41,267
or higher.

180
00:18:41,350 --> 00:18:42,518
You're very greedy.

181
00:18:42,602 --> 00:18:44,645
What if I have something

182
00:18:45,772 --> 00:18:47,231
that allows me to be greedy?

183
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,194
The Guillotine file.

184
00:18:53,446 --> 00:18:55,448
Do you know where the file is

185
00:18:56,324 --> 00:18:58,493
and who has it?

186
00:19:24,519 --> 00:19:26,062
How come there aren't any guards?

187
00:19:43,037 --> 00:19:44,497
Honey.

188
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:45,498
Seung-min!

189
00:19:45,581 --> 00:19:47,375
Honey. Seung-min.

190
00:19:47,458 --> 00:19:48,626
Honey.

191
00:19:49,502 --> 00:19:50,878
Seung-min. Honey!

192
00:19:53,714 --> 00:19:55,007
-Dad!
-Yes.

193
00:19:59,345 --> 00:20:00,513
Hello, my friend.

194
00:20:03,057 --> 00:20:04,267
-Dad.
-Yes?

195
00:20:05,059 --> 00:20:08,062
Your colleague from Italy is so handsome.

196
00:20:08,145 --> 00:20:09,689
He's my type.

197
00:20:11,107 --> 00:20:13,568
You should have told us
that he was coming today.

198
00:20:13,651 --> 00:20:15,862
-He ended up cooking everything.
-Yes.

199
00:20:15,945 --> 00:20:17,738
His spaghetti was so tasty.

200
00:20:18,656 --> 00:20:19,949
-Is that so?
-Yes.

201
00:20:20,658 --> 00:20:21,701
Seung-min.

202
00:20:23,661 --> 00:20:24,954
Did you have dinner?

203
00:20:25,997 --> 00:20:29,166
Seung-min,
I guess he hasn't had dinner yet.

204
00:20:30,585 --> 00:20:32,712
Please sit.
We have a lot of catching up to do.

205
00:20:33,462 --> 00:20:35,673
-Sit down, honey.
-Okay.

206
00:20:36,674 --> 00:20:37,842
Seung-min.

207
00:20:37,925 --> 00:20:40,219
Shall we make yummy spaghetti
for your dad, too?

208
00:20:40,303 --> 00:20:41,554
Yes.

209
00:20:41,637 --> 00:20:43,556
Can you help me cook?

210
00:20:50,187 --> 00:20:51,689
I don't care if you kill me,

211
00:20:53,941 --> 00:20:55,401
but leave my family out of this.

212
00:20:57,445 --> 00:20:59,947
Don't worry. I'm not like you.

213
00:21:01,908 --> 00:21:04,452
Is there any way I can save myself?

214
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:07,955
I'll do anything.

215
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:13,544
Do you know how you can tell
when someone's become evil?

216
00:21:14,670 --> 00:21:18,257
It's when they stop feeling ashamed.

217
00:21:18,841 --> 00:21:20,259
And you crossed that line.

218
00:21:22,094 --> 00:21:23,095
Please…

219
00:21:27,391 --> 00:21:29,352
Please don't kill me.

220
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:34,899
I don't plan on killing you yet.

221
00:21:36,025 --> 00:21:39,362
Since killing a traitor early
is an act of great generosity.

222
00:21:49,372 --> 00:21:51,165
Do whatever you want to.

223
00:21:52,041 --> 00:21:53,918
When you have everything you wanted,

224
00:21:55,002 --> 00:21:56,504
I will kill you, then.

225
00:22:05,179 --> 00:22:06,889
And cook some pasta for Seung-min.

226
00:22:08,057 --> 00:22:11,644
She said you always choose
your favorite meals when you eat out.

227
00:22:45,344 --> 00:22:46,512
Han-seo.

228
00:22:47,221 --> 00:22:50,015
Set up a meeting
with Mr. Oh Jeong-bae of Daechang Daily.

229
00:22:50,099 --> 00:22:51,142
We're not that close.

230
00:22:54,353 --> 00:22:56,689
May I ask what this is about?

231
00:22:56,772 --> 00:22:58,399
I want to talk about an article

232
00:22:58,482 --> 00:23:01,402
for our EVs and the production
of batteries by Babel Chemicals.

233
00:23:01,485 --> 00:23:04,280
Can't Director Chun take care of that?

234
00:23:05,281 --> 00:23:08,909
He won't be enough. I'm trying to get
Babel Chemicals' stocks to go up.

235
00:23:09,535 --> 00:23:10,786
I have to talk to the CEO.

236
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:12,496
But…

237
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:16,751
we're still planning to develop them.
Our technology isn't ready yet.

238
00:23:17,752 --> 00:23:19,879
I'm not saying
that we'll make cars for real.

239
00:23:20,463 --> 00:23:22,298
We'll get the stocks up and pull out.

240
00:23:25,968 --> 00:23:29,430
You are so smart. I'll never be able to
be on the same level as you.

241
00:23:29,513 --> 00:23:32,475
Cut the crap. Who was it?

242
00:23:33,642 --> 00:23:35,311
Just handle the gallery director.

243
00:23:35,394 --> 00:23:38,022
I can't have her yap
about what happened. Okay?

244
00:23:38,773 --> 00:23:41,358
Do a good job. Come on, do better.

245
00:23:53,245 --> 00:23:55,456
My hair was perfect today.

246
00:24:04,715 --> 00:24:07,343
I can't sleep
since that prosecutor betrayed us.

247
00:24:08,093 --> 00:24:09,011
Why is that?

248
00:24:09,094 --> 00:24:10,554
-Right?
-Yes.

249
00:24:11,138 --> 00:24:12,890
We're not the ones who were betrayed,

250
00:24:13,557 --> 00:24:15,684
but strangely, it upsets me so much.

251
00:24:16,811 --> 00:24:18,854
-Do you know why?
-Why is that?

252
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:22,358
We've become interested
in what's happening around us.

253
00:24:23,108 --> 00:24:27,112
We used to not care
because we were busy making a living.

254
00:24:27,196 --> 00:24:29,156
Now it feels like it's our business.

255
00:24:30,241 --> 00:24:31,784
You have a point.

256
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:35,454
We didn't care about rich people
or the law back then.

257
00:24:35,538 --> 00:24:36,956
I'm not even well-educated,

258
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:39,250
but I can see what's wrong now.

259
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:42,628
Mr. Cassano told me this
when he was straightening me out.

260
00:24:42,711 --> 00:24:46,674
"We become what we think.
If you think you're strong, you will be."

261
00:24:46,757 --> 00:24:48,008
Isn't that awesome?

262
00:24:48,092 --> 00:24:53,597
Anyway, I will follow Mr. Cassano
and continue to fight them.

263
00:24:53,681 --> 00:24:55,266
-Yes.
-Good.

264
00:24:55,349 --> 00:24:57,101
But don't get into any trouble.

265
00:24:57,184 --> 00:24:58,936
Now we might have a baby…

266
00:25:02,189 --> 00:25:03,148
What?

267
00:25:03,232 --> 00:25:06,110
Did you guys have a change of heart?

268
00:25:08,904 --> 00:25:11,907
We're going to try for a baby now.

269
00:25:11,991 --> 00:25:13,868
-My gosh.
-Goodness.

270
00:25:13,951 --> 00:25:16,120
-Great news. Have some meat.
-Oh, my.

271
00:25:16,787 --> 00:25:19,790
That way, you'll fight less and get along.

272
00:25:19,874 --> 00:25:22,126
-Goodness.
-Thank you.

273
00:25:22,918 --> 00:25:24,712
-Come on. Eat up.
-Gosh.

274
00:25:24,795 --> 00:25:26,380
That's great.

275
00:25:26,463 --> 00:25:28,757
-I bet the baby will be handsome.
-Of course.

276
00:25:28,841 --> 00:25:30,467
How was it?

277
00:25:38,183 --> 00:25:39,351
This is beautiful.

278
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,484
Mr. Cassano.

279
00:25:48,235 --> 00:25:49,361
What do you think?

280
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:52,740
It's nice.

281
00:25:53,574 --> 00:25:56,410
But didn't you already buy enough
the other day?

282
00:25:58,329 --> 00:25:59,830
It's not for me.

283
00:26:00,414 --> 00:26:02,458
I'm picking out a gift for Ms. Oh.

284
00:26:08,797 --> 00:26:12,217
Before her illness gets worse,
I want to take her out for some fresh air.

285
00:26:13,761 --> 00:26:14,762
I see.

286
00:26:18,432 --> 00:26:20,100
Won't that be too much for her?

287
00:26:20,184 --> 00:26:23,729
Her doctor said she can go out
for an hour or two.

288
00:26:23,812 --> 00:26:26,273
She hasn't gone out in ages.
She should dress up.

289
00:26:26,982 --> 00:26:30,152
You should pick one, too.
I know you have good taste.

290
00:27:12,945 --> 00:27:17,074
You bought it for her, so you should
give it to your mother yourself.

291
00:27:18,033 --> 00:27:19,618
It's fine. You should…

292
00:27:23,038 --> 00:27:24,248
Pardon?

293
00:27:24,832 --> 00:27:27,710
Why are you so surprised?
You give it to your mother.

294
00:27:37,219 --> 00:27:39,680
Did your father tell you?

295
00:27:40,764 --> 00:27:42,057
No.

296
00:27:42,141 --> 00:27:44,810
He never told me privileged information
about his clients.

297
00:27:45,686 --> 00:27:46,895
Then how did you find out?

298
00:27:49,815 --> 00:27:51,650
You paid for her medical bills.

299
00:27:51,734 --> 00:27:54,862
You got back at Shinkwang Bank for her
even if you hated acting.

300
00:27:54,945 --> 00:27:57,573
You said the same thing about
bungeoppang and ingeoppang.

301
00:27:58,157 --> 00:28:00,326
Isn't it obvious that you are her son?

302
00:28:07,166 --> 00:28:11,795
I really hate getting involved
in other people's family matters.

303
00:28:13,088 --> 00:28:14,757
But let me be nosy just this once.

304
00:28:17,384 --> 00:28:19,178
Why don't you tell her now?

305
00:28:20,179 --> 00:28:21,930
That you know you're her son.

306
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:26,018
She doesn't have much time left.

307
00:28:27,436 --> 00:28:30,397
So every single day she has left counts.

308
00:28:33,650 --> 00:28:35,152
Remember what you told me?

309
00:28:36,028 --> 00:28:38,947
"Regret is the most
painful thing in life."

310
00:28:40,783 --> 00:28:42,451
Turns out it is true.

311
00:28:43,410 --> 00:28:47,373
I hope you won't have to go through
such a painful thing.

312
00:29:08,185 --> 00:29:10,270
This looks so refined.

313
00:29:11,814 --> 00:29:13,690
I don't know if I deserve this.

314
00:29:16,568 --> 00:29:18,487
Thank you, Mr. Cassano.

315
00:29:19,655 --> 00:29:20,906
It's nothing.

316
00:29:22,282 --> 00:29:24,868
It took him an hour
to pick this bag for you.

317
00:29:25,744 --> 00:29:26,912
What?

318
00:29:27,663 --> 00:29:29,665
Gosh. You didn't have to do that.

319
00:29:32,376 --> 00:29:33,794
By the way,

320
00:29:34,878 --> 00:29:37,256
I don't think I should go out.

321
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:40,426
I'm not well.

322
00:29:41,552 --> 00:29:43,720
I'll only inconvenience you two.

323
00:29:43,804 --> 00:29:45,681
Well, I'm not coming that day.

324
00:29:45,764 --> 00:29:47,808
He will take you out.

325
00:29:48,559 --> 00:29:49,476
Right?

326
00:29:54,690 --> 00:29:55,566
Yes.

327
00:29:57,359 --> 00:30:00,696
I know you're busy. I feel awful.

328
00:30:01,738 --> 00:30:05,284
No. Think about all the places
you would like to visit.

329
00:30:06,410 --> 00:30:07,411
Okay.

330
00:30:09,705 --> 00:30:11,790
We should let her rest. Let's go.

331
00:30:16,420 --> 00:30:17,504
Ms. Hong.

332
00:30:19,798 --> 00:30:21,508
I have something to tell you.

333
00:30:25,637 --> 00:30:26,972
I would like to…

334
00:30:29,224 --> 00:30:31,602
file for a retrial.

335
00:30:35,105 --> 00:30:35,981
Really?

336
00:30:37,065 --> 00:30:38,317
Yes.

337
00:30:41,612 --> 00:30:43,780
Why the sudden change of heart?

338
00:30:45,574 --> 00:30:46,867
Actually…

339
00:30:49,119 --> 00:30:52,372
there wasn't a day
I didn't want to file for a retrial.

340
00:30:53,916 --> 00:30:55,375
I thought of doing it every day.

341
00:30:58,420 --> 00:30:59,546
But…

342
00:31:00,714 --> 00:31:02,257
I was hesitant.

343
00:31:04,009 --> 00:31:05,761
I didn't have enough courage.

344
00:31:07,638 --> 00:31:08,639
But…

345
00:31:10,849 --> 00:31:13,227
now that I'm nearing my death,

346
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,230
I finally have the courage to do it.

347
00:31:20,317 --> 00:31:22,027
Can you help me with this?

348
00:31:24,321 --> 00:31:26,031
Do you think you can do it for me?

349
00:31:31,286 --> 00:31:33,121
What do you think, Mr. Cassano?

350
00:31:34,122 --> 00:31:35,749
I'll follow your decision.

351
00:31:50,722 --> 00:31:51,723
Okay.

352
00:31:54,893 --> 00:31:55,852
Let's do it.

353
00:31:59,982 --> 00:32:01,316
I'll get started right away.

354
00:32:02,442 --> 00:32:03,652
Thank you.

355
00:32:05,654 --> 00:32:07,239
Thank you so much.

356
00:32:26,231 --> 00:32:28,150
Since your father passed away,

357
00:32:28,817 --> 00:32:30,986
you've never come to see me, you brat.

358
00:32:32,404 --> 00:32:34,198
I'm sorry. It's been hectic.

359
00:32:36,158 --> 00:32:39,328
Why are things so crazy over at Babel?

360
00:32:39,411 --> 00:32:42,789
Daechang has been working our butt off
to cover for you.

361
00:32:43,373 --> 00:32:44,458
I'll return the favor.

362
00:32:45,584 --> 00:32:48,503
-Han-seo already told you, right?
-Yes.

363
00:32:48,587 --> 00:32:51,590
You want an editorial about
Babel Chemicals' battery production.

364
00:32:53,258 --> 00:32:54,885
But Han-seok,

365
00:32:54,968 --> 00:32:58,430
even elementary school kids
invest in stocks nowadays.

366
00:32:58,513 --> 00:33:00,390
This is a sensitive and risky move.

367
00:33:02,184 --> 00:33:03,936
But you did it for my dad.

368
00:33:04,853 --> 00:33:06,230
Just do what you did for him.

369
00:33:12,819 --> 00:33:15,072
Why does a beautiful woman like you

370
00:33:16,114 --> 00:33:18,408
need to flee the country this urgently?

371
00:33:19,993 --> 00:33:20,911
I have made…

372
00:33:22,454 --> 00:33:25,165
a terrible mistake.

373
00:33:26,124 --> 00:33:28,627
I can't make up for it even with my life.

374
00:33:30,337 --> 00:33:32,256
That's awful.

375
00:33:33,632 --> 00:33:34,883
Don't worry too much.

376
00:33:35,717 --> 00:33:36,927
Actually, we have a spot,

377
00:33:37,511 --> 00:33:39,304
so you can leave later today.

378
00:33:40,472 --> 00:33:43,558
You're certain that
it's a direct flight to Taiwan, right?

379
00:33:43,642 --> 00:33:48,063
Of course. The wind is strong today.
You could go to Cebu if you wanted.

380
00:33:48,146 --> 00:33:51,024
Is it possible to end up
flying past the destination?

381
00:33:52,150 --> 00:33:55,237
It is quite random, to tell you the truth.

382
00:33:55,320 --> 00:33:56,488
If you don't want to…

383
00:33:56,571 --> 00:33:58,282
-Hey--
-I'll take it!

384
00:33:59,324 --> 00:34:01,451
Yes, that's the contract.
Read it carefully.

385
00:34:03,412 --> 00:34:05,038
BYEBYE BALLOON
TRAVEL CONTRACT

386
00:34:05,956 --> 00:34:08,750
We have a client here.
What is it this time?

387
00:34:09,876 --> 00:34:11,962
I just got a stock investment tip.

388
00:34:12,045 --> 00:34:14,089
Daechang is preparing
to publish an article

389
00:34:14,172 --> 00:34:15,674
to promote Babel Chemicals.

390
00:34:16,633 --> 00:34:18,677
It's about EVs and batteries.

391
00:34:20,762 --> 00:34:22,889
-Excuse me. Read the contract.
-Okay.

392
00:34:23,724 --> 00:34:25,600
I should buy Babel Chemicals' stocks.

393
00:34:32,733 --> 00:34:34,651
These Babel assholes won't die.

394
00:34:35,235 --> 00:34:37,279
They are getting richer instead.

395
00:34:37,362 --> 00:34:38,947
How? Why is that?

396
00:34:41,241 --> 00:34:42,993
Everyone, do you want some coffee?

397
00:34:43,076 --> 00:34:45,162
I'm not in the mood to drink coffee now.

398
00:34:45,245 --> 00:34:47,414
I'm not in the mood to make coffee now.

399
00:34:47,998 --> 00:34:48,999
Okay.

400
00:34:57,049 --> 00:34:59,426
Gosh. That traitor, Jung.

401
00:35:00,177 --> 00:35:02,596
Babel will get more powerful
because of that bastard.

402
00:35:03,305 --> 00:35:06,892
You met him last night. Why didn't you
make him pay for what he did?

403
00:35:06,975 --> 00:35:08,852
He will do that in installments.

404
00:35:11,813 --> 00:35:13,023
Do you think it's possible

405
00:35:13,106 --> 00:35:15,317
he's just pretending to have switch sides?

406
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,902
Maybe he wants to expose

407
00:35:16,985 --> 00:35:19,071
-all the secrets from within--
-Mr. Nam.

408
00:35:20,197 --> 00:35:23,450
That's never happened
in the history of this country.

409
00:35:24,826 --> 00:35:26,453
We don't need Prosecutor Jung.

410
00:35:28,205 --> 00:35:29,289
What's that?

411
00:35:31,458 --> 00:35:32,334
This?

412
00:35:34,169 --> 00:35:35,545
The Guillotine file.

413
00:35:36,380 --> 00:35:37,422
The Guillotine file.

414
00:35:38,382 --> 00:35:41,843
You said you accidentally threw it
in the secret room and closed the door.

415
00:35:41,927 --> 00:35:43,220
Who said that? Me?

416
00:35:43,303 --> 00:35:45,889
-Yes.
-Did I say that?

417
00:36:12,416 --> 00:36:15,836
My goodness. Vincenzo Cassano.

418
00:36:15,919 --> 00:36:17,754
Let's reveal what's in the file.

419
00:36:17,838 --> 00:36:21,133
Once it goes online,
it'll go international in an hour.

420
00:36:21,216 --> 00:36:22,968
-That's not a good idea.
-Why not?

421
00:36:23,051 --> 00:36:25,137
It'll last a few days. But…

422
00:36:25,762 --> 00:36:29,182
no one that's in this file
will pay for what they did.

423
00:36:30,434 --> 00:36:33,061
This file wasn't created
to expose the truth to the world

424
00:36:33,645 --> 00:36:36,773
but for evil men to exploit the weakness
of other evil men.

425
00:36:37,482 --> 00:36:39,860
Only an evil man can use it properly.

426
00:36:39,943 --> 00:36:41,862
And we can use it just like they would.

427
00:36:41,945 --> 00:36:44,573
We'll keep them on a leash
and order them around.

428
00:36:45,490 --> 00:36:46,658
I see.

429
00:36:47,576 --> 00:36:49,035
How frightening.

430
00:36:51,872 --> 00:36:54,249
Did you read the file?

431
00:36:54,833 --> 00:36:55,792
No. Not yet.

432
00:36:56,334 --> 00:36:57,919
I wanted us to read it together.

433
00:36:58,712 --> 00:36:59,629
Mr. Nam.

434
00:36:59,713 --> 00:37:02,007
-The laptop!
-Right, the laptop!

435
00:37:15,103 --> 00:37:18,106
Gosh. Something doesn't feel right.

436
00:37:19,357 --> 00:37:23,695
I'm sure Prosecutor Jung and Mr. Jang
made a deal over something.

437
00:37:24,279 --> 00:37:28,325
You know, the file.
The file they got from the gallery.

438
00:37:29,034 --> 00:37:30,994
Do you think that's all?

439
00:37:31,077 --> 00:37:32,829
That should be more than enough.

440
00:37:33,788 --> 00:37:34,956
He has my brother

441
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:38,418
on tax evasion, illegally acquired stocks,
and everything on that file.

442
00:37:38,502 --> 00:37:40,128
No. I get the feeling

443
00:37:41,505 --> 00:37:42,881
that there's more.

444
00:37:43,632 --> 00:37:45,675
What else? What else could there…

445
00:37:48,220 --> 00:37:49,554
Is there really more?

446
00:37:53,433 --> 00:37:55,977
-I don't know that.
-Me neither.

447
00:37:57,896 --> 00:38:00,899
Anyway, Jung is
on your brother's side now.

448
00:38:00,982 --> 00:38:04,027
And the deal with Daechang Daily
went smoothly.

449
00:38:04,653 --> 00:38:08,949
Now your brother is going
to become powerful beyond control.

450
00:38:16,581 --> 00:38:18,208
PROSECUTION

451
00:38:21,378 --> 00:38:24,673
Gosh. The tabloids are nothing
compared to this.

452
00:38:24,756 --> 00:38:26,049
It is unbelievable.

453
00:38:26,132 --> 00:38:29,719
To get this kind of information,
they must've surveilled them illegally.

454
00:38:30,554 --> 00:38:32,764
This time, we'll be targeting Babel

455
00:38:33,348 --> 00:38:35,183
-and Daechang Daily.
-Daechang Daily.

456
00:38:35,267 --> 00:38:37,978
I've been waiting
to crush this trashy agency.

457
00:38:38,061 --> 00:38:40,689
Back in the day, newspapers could be
used as toilet paper.

458
00:38:40,772 --> 00:38:43,108
But now, there's no use for them.

459
00:38:43,191 --> 00:38:47,153
I mean, this so-called newspaper
makes ridiculous claims all year round.

460
00:38:47,237 --> 00:38:48,863
They're absurd and make no sense.

461
00:38:48,947 --> 00:38:52,284
If they keep doing it,
it is their attitude. It'll never change.

462
00:38:52,367 --> 00:38:55,996
If Daechang Daily is gone,
it will cleanse our eyes and ears.

463
00:38:56,079 --> 00:38:59,833
First, I'm planning to make them
fight and destroy each other.

464
00:39:00,625 --> 00:39:03,503
Each other? How will you
make them go after each other?

465
00:39:04,963 --> 00:39:05,839
Don't forget.

466
00:39:07,424 --> 00:39:10,135
We have this Guillotine file.

467
00:39:10,218 --> 00:39:13,054
Right, we'll pit one evil against another.

468
00:39:14,931 --> 00:39:17,017
All right. Look over here.

469
00:39:36,620 --> 00:39:38,455
Well, your office is…

470
00:39:39,539 --> 00:39:42,334
It looks lame and awkward. It's nice.

471
00:39:44,711 --> 00:39:45,837
Why are you here?

472
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,881
What? I can come if I want to.

473
00:39:55,388 --> 00:39:59,059
It's nothing much. It's just
the most expensive coffee, Kopi Luwak.

474
00:39:59,142 --> 00:40:00,518
I'm sure you know what it is.

475
00:40:00,602 --> 00:40:03,563
It's a rare product
made from civets' poop.

476
00:40:03,647 --> 00:40:04,856
What a load of crap.

477
00:40:07,776 --> 00:40:08,985
Who is that guy?

478
00:40:09,903 --> 00:40:13,448
I'm not sure if Vincenzo is just lucky

479
00:40:13,531 --> 00:40:15,992
or he's really competent.
But he's impressive.

480
00:40:16,576 --> 00:40:18,870
The Guillotine file and 15 tons of gold.

481
00:40:19,454 --> 00:40:21,331
No one will even think that it's there.

482
00:40:21,414 --> 00:40:22,999
If we can get the file,

483
00:40:23,792 --> 00:40:26,753
all the powerful people in Korea
will kneel

484
00:40:27,545 --> 00:40:29,255
before you.

485
00:40:33,343 --> 00:40:35,804
It sounds like the One Ring
from The Lord of the Rings.

486
00:40:36,471 --> 00:40:38,098
You watched it, so you must know.

487
00:40:38,890 --> 00:40:41,643
If it falls into the wrong hands,
it'll cause problems.

488
00:40:42,310 --> 00:40:43,770
Only people like us

489
00:40:44,938 --> 00:40:47,273
will do justice to the Ring.

490
00:40:55,615 --> 00:40:57,826
Let's demolish Geumga Plaza
as fast as we can.

491
00:40:58,576 --> 00:41:00,453
That way, we can get the file out.

492
00:41:02,247 --> 00:41:05,166
I'll give you some of the gold
in the secret room.

493
00:41:06,084 --> 00:41:07,127
Sure.

494
00:41:07,877 --> 00:41:09,254
I'll gladly accept it.

495
00:41:13,258 --> 00:41:14,092
Thank you.

496
00:41:15,468 --> 00:41:16,636
Thank you.

497
00:41:19,681 --> 00:41:20,682
Hey, wait.

498
00:41:21,558 --> 00:41:24,477
Why didn't you make the coffee
that I brought?

499
00:41:24,561 --> 00:41:26,521
We don't have a coffee maker.

500
00:41:28,022 --> 00:41:31,317
Gosh. Your working conditions here
are awful.

501
00:41:33,403 --> 00:41:36,072
Damn it. It's so bitter. Hey, dude.
Why is this so bitter?

502
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:48,501
I heard that you asked Mr. Cassano
to get rid of your own brother.

503
00:41:48,585 --> 00:41:50,962
It would have all worked out
if he did what I asked.

504
00:41:51,045 --> 00:41:53,882
Things have gotten worse
because you declined.

505
00:41:54,466 --> 00:41:55,425
Didn't I tell you?

506
00:41:55,508 --> 00:41:57,761
I never exploit betrayals within a family.

507
00:41:59,763 --> 00:42:02,056
I forgot to tell you this
because I was flustered.

508
00:42:03,933 --> 00:42:06,561
I'm not trying to betray my own brother.

509
00:42:07,937 --> 00:42:08,897
What I want…

510
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:11,566
How should I put it?
I don't want people to die anymore.

511
00:42:11,649 --> 00:42:15,236
-Right.
-I'm trying to run Babel legally.

512
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:19,657
I guess you've been studying a lot.
Your vocabulary has gotten better.

513
00:42:20,617 --> 00:42:22,786
Let me get this straight. You want to run

514
00:42:23,369 --> 00:42:25,872
the company properly
after getting rid of your brother?

515
00:42:25,955 --> 00:42:27,332
-That's it.
-Okay.

516
00:42:28,750 --> 00:42:30,960
I really love Babel.

517
00:42:31,044 --> 00:42:33,296
I want to run the company the right way.

518
00:42:33,379 --> 00:42:36,299
I really don't want people to get killed.
I mean that.

519
