779
00:58:01,265 --> 00:58:02,808
My hands are freezing.

780
00:58:03,475 --> 00:58:04,476
I'm so cold.

781
00:58:10,232 --> 00:58:12,609
How could you push me off
the cliff and leave me?

782
00:58:12,693 --> 00:58:14,653
I'm still here.

783
00:58:21,785 --> 00:58:22,661
How…

784
00:58:23,996 --> 00:58:26,749
-How could my brother…
-I'm cold.

785
00:58:29,209 --> 00:58:31,670
Jeong-bae, help me up already.

786
00:58:32,838 --> 00:58:34,882
It's freezing down here. Okay?

787
00:58:35,549 --> 00:58:37,885
-I'm so cold, Jeong-bae.
-Go away.

788
00:58:37,968 --> 00:58:40,387
-Get away from me.
-Jeong-bae.

789
00:58:40,471 --> 00:58:43,182
-Get off me.
-Jeong-bae.

790
00:58:44,475 --> 00:58:46,935
Jeong-bae.

791
00:58:47,019 --> 00:58:48,228
-Let go.
-Jeong-bae.

792
00:58:48,312 --> 00:58:50,522
-No!
-Jeong-bae.

793
00:58:50,606 --> 00:58:52,149
-Go away.
-I'm cold, Jeong-bae.

794
00:58:52,232 --> 00:58:55,402
Jeong-bae, I'm so cold.

795
00:58:55,486 --> 00:58:57,237
Get away from me!

796
00:58:57,321 --> 00:58:59,281
Jeong-bae, I'm so cold.

797
00:59:04,077 --> 00:59:05,329
Why are there

798
00:59:06,789 --> 00:59:09,833
so many burdens in my life?

799
00:59:11,668 --> 00:59:15,047
It's not that you have many burdens.
You are just weak.

800
00:59:16,465 --> 00:59:18,675
The weaker you are,

801
00:59:19,551 --> 00:59:22,304
the heavier your burdens become.

802
00:59:23,472 --> 00:59:24,681
I see.

803
00:59:25,557 --> 00:59:29,269
Do you want to see
what will kill you eventually?

804
00:59:30,854 --> 00:59:33,023
Yes. I do.

805
01:00:10,978 --> 01:00:12,813
BABEL

806
01:00:22,823 --> 01:00:26,577
Unless you cut ties with Babel,
you will die a miserable death.

807
01:00:30,706 --> 01:00:32,124
Is that all I need to do?

808
01:00:36,795 --> 01:00:39,006
It's more than cutting ties with them.

809
01:00:40,382 --> 01:00:44,011
You must cut ties with them
as you completely trample on them.

810
01:00:44,094 --> 01:00:45,304
What?

811
01:00:45,387 --> 01:00:46,930
To get rid of bad luck altogether.

812
01:00:48,974 --> 01:00:49,975
That's…

813
01:00:50,642 --> 01:00:53,312
It's not that easy.

814
01:01:10,162 --> 01:01:11,663
I see.

815
01:01:15,208 --> 01:01:17,044
That's the number of days you have left.

816
01:01:18,378 --> 01:01:19,296
Five days.

817
01:01:28,555 --> 01:01:30,390
Poor thing.

818
01:01:42,069 --> 01:01:43,153
You know what?

819
01:01:43,904 --> 01:01:47,532
I went too hard earlier.
My arms are hurting. They hurt so much.

820
01:01:50,744 --> 01:01:52,704
Isn't it ironic?

821
01:01:52,788 --> 01:01:56,458
A newspaper company is supposed to
publish facts, but he's so superstitious.

822
01:01:57,626 --> 01:02:01,296
He's superstitious
because he has no interest in facts.

823
01:02:05,550 --> 01:02:06,718
You startled me.

824
01:02:06,802 --> 01:02:07,719
Oh, right.

825
01:02:07,803 --> 01:02:12,057
I forgot to tell you
because we were so busy today.

826
01:02:12,140 --> 01:02:15,477
I found something shocking about
Jang Han-seok in the Guillotine file.

827
01:02:16,228 --> 01:02:18,021
-What is it?
-Chairman Jang

828
01:02:18,772 --> 01:02:21,441
killed four of his classmates
in middle and high school.

829
01:02:23,902 --> 01:02:27,781
He brought classmates he didn't like
to a rooftop and made them jump.

830
01:02:27,864 --> 01:02:30,993
Or he hunted and killed them
in the mountains like they were prey.

831
01:02:32,077 --> 01:02:36,999
He killed the last one because he stole
a ball from him during a gym class.

832
01:02:37,582 --> 01:02:40,752
Jang used the goal net to strangle him.

833
01:02:43,046 --> 01:02:44,631
Here's what's scarier.

834
01:03:00,564 --> 01:03:01,732
JANG HAN-SEOK

835
01:03:28,675 --> 01:03:30,594
He took the deceased's watches

836
01:03:30,677 --> 01:03:33,180
as some kind of a trophy.

837
01:03:34,097 --> 01:03:37,809
And he even bragged about it
like he was proud of it.

838
01:03:39,519 --> 01:03:41,146
He's a psychopath.

839
01:03:41,229 --> 01:03:44,149
He was diagnosed as a psychopath
at the age of 16.

840
01:03:44,232 --> 01:03:47,611
That's why his father sent him
to the States

841
01:03:47,694 --> 01:03:50,072
fearing that he might become
a serial killer.

842
01:03:50,155 --> 01:03:53,158
Jang Han-seo was beaten
and tortured by him,

843
01:03:53,241 --> 01:03:56,495
so he's been seeing a therapist
ever since he was little.

844
01:03:56,578 --> 01:03:59,039
And that's how he ended up doing drugs.

845
01:03:59,122 --> 01:04:01,374
Even so, he shouldn't be doing drugs.

846
01:04:01,458 --> 01:04:02,959
That jerk.

847
01:04:03,043 --> 01:04:04,795
Anyway, their father, Jang Guk-hwan,

848
01:04:05,462 --> 01:04:07,380
covered everything up with money

849
01:04:08,090 --> 01:04:09,174
and kept it a secret.

850
01:04:13,178 --> 01:04:15,555
That explains why he was so hard to beat.

851
01:04:17,224 --> 01:04:18,475
Turns out he's

852
01:04:19,851 --> 01:04:21,311
the biggest monster of them all.

853
01:04:30,028 --> 01:04:32,656
BABEL SUSPECTED TO HAVE MADE
FALSE STATEMENTS TO RAISE STOCK VALUE

854
01:04:51,299 --> 01:04:52,467
DAECHANG DAILY

855
01:04:54,761 --> 01:04:55,762
Hello?

856
01:04:55,846 --> 01:04:57,222
What are you doing?

857
01:04:58,056 --> 01:05:00,267
-What the hell is this?
-Mr. Jang.

858
01:05:00,350 --> 01:05:05,272
There has been a change
in the guidelines at my company.

859
01:05:06,148 --> 01:05:08,233
Did I do something to offend you?

860
01:05:08,316 --> 01:05:10,235
No, you didn't.

861
01:05:10,318 --> 01:05:14,906
Now Daechang Daily is an honest newspaper
that only speaks the truth.

862
01:05:14,990 --> 01:05:15,949
The truth?

863
01:05:16,533 --> 01:05:19,953
You're the most corrupt newspaper company
in Korea. But what? The truth?

864
01:05:20,036 --> 01:05:21,788
Watch what you say.

865
01:05:21,872 --> 01:05:23,999
So, why didn't you
run your company properly?

866
01:05:24,499 --> 01:05:25,667
I'm hanging up.

867
01:05:25,750 --> 01:05:27,419
Mr. Oh? Mr. Oh!

868
01:05:28,003 --> 01:05:28,879
Hey!

869
01:05:44,227 --> 01:05:47,772
How come my days are still numbered?

870
01:05:47,856 --> 01:05:51,026
I just cut all ties with Babel.

871
01:05:51,109 --> 01:05:53,820
That won't be enough to save your life.

872
01:05:53,904 --> 01:05:55,113
Pardon?

873
01:05:56,072 --> 01:06:00,619
Then what more do I need to do?

874
01:06:02,662 --> 01:06:04,789
The owner of Babel.

875
01:06:04,873 --> 01:06:05,916
The king of Babel.

876
01:06:11,254 --> 01:06:12,547
Are you talking about

877
01:06:12,631 --> 01:06:15,258
Chairman Jang Han-seok?

878
01:06:16,635 --> 01:06:18,887
He's the one
who's holding onto your misfortune.

879
01:06:20,472 --> 01:06:23,475
If you expose his past evils,

880
01:06:23,558 --> 01:06:26,937
and relieve the spirits that wander
the realm of the living because of him,

881
01:06:27,687 --> 01:06:30,690
those spirits will help you.

882
01:06:38,865 --> 01:06:41,409
The wandering spirits?

883
01:06:47,832 --> 01:06:51,086
Are you saying Han-seok killed someone?

884
01:07:15,402 --> 01:07:16,569
Han-seok.

885
01:07:18,071 --> 01:07:19,781
I'm sorry.

886
01:07:19,864 --> 01:07:21,574
Don't hit me.

887
01:07:21,658 --> 01:07:25,245
Han-seok. I'm sorry.

888
01:07:25,328 --> 01:07:26,496
It's all my fault.

889
01:07:26,579 --> 01:07:28,164
-I'm not Han-seok.
-I'm sorry.

890
01:07:28,248 --> 01:07:29,708
-I'm not him.
-Don't strangle me.

891
01:07:29,791 --> 01:07:31,751
-I can't breathe.
-Jang Han-seok.

892
01:07:31,835 --> 01:07:32,877
Don't strangle me.

893
01:07:32,961 --> 01:07:34,713
-Jang Han-seok. Spare me.
-No.

894
01:07:34,796 --> 01:07:36,381
-It's my fault.
-Don't do it.

895
01:07:36,464 --> 01:07:38,591
No. I'm not Han-seok!

896
01:07:38,675 --> 01:07:39,926
That's my watch.

897
01:07:40,010 --> 01:07:42,595
That's my watch. It's mine.

898
01:07:42,679 --> 01:07:45,140
-It's my watch.
-No.

899
01:07:46,975 --> 01:07:51,354
The chairman of Babel,
one of the biggest companies in Korea,

900
01:07:51,438 --> 01:07:52,814
was a bully?

901
01:07:52,897 --> 01:07:55,317
No. It was more of a massacre.

902
01:07:55,900 --> 01:07:58,987
This has come
as shocking news to the public.

903
01:07:59,070 --> 01:08:02,198
On top of that,
he was never punished for his crimes,

904
01:08:02,282 --> 01:08:05,952
and was able to climb the ladder
to become the chairman.

905
01:08:06,578 --> 01:08:09,122
I mean, seriously?
Where were the police and prosecutors

906
01:08:09,205 --> 01:08:11,124
in all of this?

907
01:08:11,833 --> 01:08:13,585
Right now, a lot of people

908
01:08:13,668 --> 01:08:16,671
are urging this killer chairman
to be punished

909
01:08:16,755 --> 01:08:19,632
on many of the online forums
and petitioning for it as well.

910
01:08:20,216 --> 01:08:21,509
Gosh.

911
01:08:22,635 --> 01:08:24,554
How did they know?

912
01:08:24,637 --> 01:08:28,767
Even Mr. Oh wouldn't
know about my childhood.

913
01:08:28,850 --> 01:08:31,394
…update you with a follow-up coverage.

914
01:08:31,478 --> 01:08:33,021
Right now, Babel Group

915
01:08:33,104 --> 01:08:34,939
-has dismissed the claims
-Hey.

916
01:08:35,023 --> 01:08:36,608
-It wasn't you, right?
-as being false.

917
01:08:36,691 --> 01:08:39,903
-They will soon release
-What? Of course, it wasn't me.

918
01:08:39,986 --> 01:08:43,531
The article even said I was crazy
and did drugs. You think I did that?

919
01:08:45,283 --> 01:08:46,618
Well, you're right.

920
01:08:49,371 --> 01:08:53,875
It was reported that there hadn't been
an investigation on this in the past.

921
01:08:55,377 --> 01:08:57,879
Who else knows about this?

922
01:08:59,756 --> 01:09:03,176
My dad, the detective who worked the case,

923
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:05,178
and the prosecutor in charge.

924
01:09:07,680 --> 01:09:11,601
Then there's a source we're not aware of.

925
01:09:12,352 --> 01:09:16,022
The problem is the intention.
Why is Mr. Oh attacking you now?

926
01:09:16,606 --> 01:09:19,025
It looks like
he's trying to bring me down.

927
01:09:35,583 --> 01:09:39,504
LIFE

928
01:09:52,350 --> 01:09:54,018
It's all done.

929
01:09:54,769 --> 01:09:56,229
You have been spared.

930
01:10:02,777 --> 01:10:05,488
Fate has a weakness for brave souls,

931
01:10:06,030 --> 01:10:08,324
but it can be a powerful foe
to those who are weak.

932
01:10:10,285 --> 01:10:13,037
You have been brave
and averted this crisis.

933
01:10:44,402 --> 01:10:46,821
Thank you.

934
01:10:48,072 --> 01:10:50,450
Thank you.

935
01:11:12,680 --> 01:11:14,098
It's been a while, Mr. Cho.

936
01:11:14,182 --> 01:11:15,683
Can we meet now?

937
01:11:15,767 --> 01:11:18,061
I'll meet you at the parking lot
of the plaza.

938
01:11:19,187 --> 01:11:21,189
Okay. Sure.

939
01:11:22,190 --> 01:11:23,107
Okay.

940
01:12:48,943 --> 01:12:49,944
Run!

941
01:12:57,076 --> 01:12:58,453
Who are they?

942
01:12:59,078 --> 01:13:02,040
I think Prosecutor Jung sent them.

943
01:13:03,875 --> 01:13:04,917
Prosecutor Jung?

944
01:13:08,671 --> 01:13:10,548
It's as expected.

945
01:13:10,632 --> 01:13:12,884
It was Vincenzo.

946
01:13:12,967 --> 01:13:16,137
He exploited Mr. Oh's tendency
to have blind faith in shamans.

947
01:13:16,804 --> 01:13:18,514
He's so detailed.

948
01:13:20,224 --> 01:13:22,560
I really can't beat a Mafia member.

949
01:13:24,354 --> 01:13:25,688
Anyway…

950
01:13:25,772 --> 01:13:29,442
how did he find out
what happened when I was young?

951
01:13:30,109 --> 01:13:32,445
That's still a mystery to me.

952
01:13:32,528 --> 01:13:36,199
But it's most likely that he got it
from the intelligence agency.

953
01:13:38,368 --> 01:13:40,995
How on earth did he find out?

954
01:13:41,579 --> 01:13:43,665
Given the current circumstances,

955
01:13:43,748 --> 01:13:46,876
he's pitted Babel and Daechang
against each other.

956
01:13:46,959 --> 01:13:50,713
Even so. Mr. Oh of all people
can't do that to me.

957
01:13:52,090 --> 01:13:53,174
What should we do?

958
01:13:57,220 --> 01:14:01,182
Make Vincenzo end it himself.

959
01:14:01,265 --> 01:14:03,810
Oh, right. I must show you something.

960
01:14:07,438 --> 01:14:08,356
What is it?

961
01:14:09,857 --> 01:14:12,360
Vincenzo's Korean name is Park Ju-hyeong.

962
01:14:12,443 --> 01:14:15,571
He was adopted after being abandoned
by his mother when he was little.

963
01:14:15,655 --> 01:14:16,906
OH GYEONG-JA, PERSONAL DETAILS

964
01:14:16,989 --> 01:14:18,199
Is his mom alive?

965
01:14:18,282 --> 01:14:21,202
She is. But she recently got out of prison

966
01:14:21,285 --> 01:14:23,621
-because of pancreatic cancer.
-What was she in for?

967
01:14:23,705 --> 01:14:26,124
She was the housekeeper
who was involved in the death

968
01:14:26,207 --> 01:14:28,668
of Shinkwang Finance's Chairman Hwang.

969
01:14:30,128 --> 01:14:31,295
NAMDONGBU DISTRICT COURT
RULING

970
01:14:31,379 --> 01:14:32,255
Wait.

971
01:14:32,755 --> 01:14:35,633
He ruined the signing ceremony
a while ago.

972
01:14:38,970 --> 01:14:40,763
Is this why he did that?

973
01:14:40,847 --> 01:14:41,889
Yes.

974
01:14:42,890 --> 01:14:46,102
Hong Yu-chan was the public defender
who took her case.

975
01:14:46,185 --> 01:14:50,732
And today, she filed for a retrial
regarding the death of Hwang Deok-bae.

976
01:14:50,815 --> 01:14:51,983
A retrial?

977
01:14:53,985 --> 01:14:56,112
-Who filed it?
-Cha-young did.

978
01:14:56,195 --> 01:14:58,573
Of course, Vincenzo must be behind it.

979
01:15:04,495 --> 01:15:07,582
That means Vincenzo
has been spending time with his mother.

980
01:15:07,665 --> 01:15:12,462
I'm trying to find out which hospital
his mother is being treated in.

981
01:15:19,302 --> 01:15:22,764
I met Jung at the International Security
Intelligence Service five years ago.

982
01:15:23,514 --> 01:15:26,768
He was dispatched for a case,
and I had a desk job there.

983
01:15:27,518 --> 01:15:30,021
We found out the true nature
of the Guillotine file,

984
01:15:30,104 --> 01:15:31,439
and Jung thought he could

985
01:15:31,522 --> 01:15:34,567
root out all corruption in Korea
with the file.

986
01:15:35,151 --> 01:15:37,445
So he desperately tried
to get his hands on it,

987
01:15:37,528 --> 01:15:39,572
and I joined hands with him.

988
01:15:40,865 --> 01:15:42,950
That was before he went dirty.

989
01:15:43,034 --> 01:15:43,993
Yes.

990
01:15:44,952 --> 01:15:47,330
But soon,
the file was hacked and vanished,

991
01:15:47,413 --> 01:15:49,707
and I volunteered to look for the file.

992
01:15:51,083 --> 01:15:52,710
That's how I got here.

993
01:15:53,878 --> 01:15:56,839
But Jung has betrayed you, right?

994
01:15:57,507 --> 01:16:01,636
Yes. In fact, I suspected him
these past few months.

995
01:16:02,220 --> 01:16:05,640
I felt he had an ulterior motive
for looking for the file.

996
01:16:08,392 --> 01:16:11,729
Now that he is on Jang Han-seok's side,
he must know by now

997
01:16:12,522 --> 01:16:15,983
that the file and the gold are here.

998
01:16:16,067 --> 01:16:20,321
And he must know he has to demolish
the plaza to retrieve them.

999
01:16:28,371 --> 01:16:29,914
GEUMGA PLAZA

1000
01:17:01,904 --> 01:17:04,323
PETITION FOR A RETRIAL

1001
01:18:09,013 --> 01:18:09,972
Damn it.

1002
01:19:43,107 --> 01:19:44,567
Mr. Vincenzo Cassano.

1003
01:19:44,650 --> 01:19:47,528
You're under arrest
for the murder of Oh Jeong-bae.

1004
01:20:22,480 --> 01:20:24,231
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE HYE-JUNG
AND IM SUNG-JAE

1005
01:20:52,927 --> 01:20:54,345
It was a setup, wasn't it?

1006
01:20:55,054 --> 01:20:57,431
Then we'll have to use
the most effective method.

1007
01:20:57,515 --> 01:20:58,724
I'll make sure no one ever gets it.

1008
01:20:58,808 --> 01:21:00,559
I have to find the person who lured me.

1009
01:21:00,643 --> 01:21:03,354
I'll make sure everyone who tried to
build it will be punished.

1010
01:21:03,437 --> 01:21:07,191
He could stir up the entire nation.

1011
01:21:08,442 --> 01:21:11,320
To cherish Geumga Plaza
as a historical building.

1012
01:21:12,279 --> 01:21:14,073
Make him pay.

1013
01:21:15,324 --> 01:21:16,784
It's time for you to die.

1014
01:21:16,867 --> 01:21:20,788
You will die a slow death,
experiencing it every step of the way.

1015
01:21:22,540 --> 01:21:27,545
Subtitle translation by: Won-hyang Son
